# Output Generation Schema

For each unique accessibility violation discovered during the analysis, you must output the diagnostic data strictly utilizing the following Markdown formatting structure. Do not deviate from this schema.

**Issue:**
**WCAG Criterion:** [e.g., 1.1.1 Non-Text Content]
**Level:** [A | AA]
**Axe Rule ID:** [e.g., `image-alt` — include when applicable, "Manual check" otherwise]
**Page or file it occurs:** [Provide the absolute or relative file path within the repository]
**Line(s):** [Line number(s) or range where the violation occurs]
**Severity:** [Critical | High | Medium | Low]
**Impact:** [Describe who is affected — screen reader users, keyboard users, low-vision users, motor-impaired users, cognitive disability users, etc.]
**Suggest fixes:** [Provide specific code-level remediation with before/after examples when possible]
